name: Neil Harris
summary: Millwall head coach Neil Harris has announced his resignation from the role, effective this weekend. Harris previously led Millwall as manager from 2015 to 2019, before returning for a second stint in 2021. His decision comes following a series of disappointing results, including a recent loss to Coventry City that prompted Harris to criticize a section of the club's supporters as "thickos." Millwall chairman John Berylson has expressed gratitude for Harris's contributions, stating that he "steered the club away from the relegation zone." Despite the club's improved league position, Harris has cited a lack of long-term support as a factor in his departure. The board of Millwall has re-iterated its commitment to the club's future and will now begin the search for a new head coach.
